premise_source_doc_sentence: AC/DC released 17 studio albums  (  15 available worldwide and 2 released only in Australia  )  , 2 soundtrack albums , 4 live albums , 11 video albums , and 2 box-set albums .

Although a large number of AC/DC singles have been released , the band always refused to release any greatest-hits type packages ; Who Made Who  (  which served as the soundtrack to Stephen King 's Maximum Overdrive  )  , Iron Man 2 , and the band 's various live recordings are as close as the group have come to such a compilation .
